HEADWORD: Cymogene
<hw>Cy"mo*gene</hw> <pr>(s?"m?-j?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A highly volatile liquid, condensed by cold and
pressure from the first products of the distillation of petroleum; --
used for producing low temperatures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

